Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specify_cell_stack_area(25.10)                  specify_cell_stack_area(25.10)

Name
       specify_cell_stack_area  -  Defines  the cell area that needs to be in-
       volved while calculating stack rule of the corresponding group

Syntax
       specify_cell_stack_area

       [-help]

       -cell <cell_name>

       -group <group_name>

       -rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}

       Defines the cell area that needs to be involved while calculating stack
       rule of the corresponding group.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the cell name that has the stack constraint.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each specify_cell_stack_area parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specify_cell_stack_area

       -group <group_name>
              Specifies the cell group name with the stack constraint.

              Note:  The  group name must be pre-defined in the LEF file or by
              the specify_cell_stack_group command

       -rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}
              Specifies the constraint rectangular area with  respect  to  the
              cell origin.

              If  the  whole  cell is constrained, the rectangular coordinates
              match the cell boundary. If the rectilinear area in cell is con-
              strained, divide the rectilinear area into multiple  rectangular
              area  then  define  each  rectangular  area  in separate command
              lines.

Related Information
